{"TopicId":210667,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Symmetric mode with custom number of symmetric parts","CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-17T20:46:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-17T20:46:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the KSP you have constant value of different types of radial simmetry (radial n-symmetry, where n = 2, 3, 4, 6, 8). I suggest that it is possible to make unlimited number, so you use all numbers, for example 5, 7, 9, 10, 13 and others (imagine 28 or 33-symmetry!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI think this feature could be implemented as a line (e.g. in the bottom left corner as usual) that shows the number of symmetry and circle, divided into n parts. This parameter\u00A0can be changed by entering another number from the keyboard to the line\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI belive that realisation of this function will be very easy (just attach each part through the corner 360 / n automatically), except problem with big numbers, where details\u00A0can cross each other. The most important that it is of course obviously make construction much more comfortable and you don\u0027t need to use several times one n-symmetry mode and\u00A0level parts by eye (I think you can also level details in new\u00A0 scheme mode?).\u00A0\u00A0It would be nice to see this feature in ksp2, which would make the constructor even closer to the ideal;)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-19T12:57:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can already have any symmetry in KSP\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-19T15:08:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224200462\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210667\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221668862649\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nazalassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nazalassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can already have any symmetry in KSP\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the suggestion is for it to become a normal part of the UI instead of a strange workaround.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-19T15:28:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224200462\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210667\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221668862649\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nazalassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nazalassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can already have any symmetry in KSP\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, if you rely on an exploit that probably won\u0027t exist in KSP 2...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-26T23:46:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224200462\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210667\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquot